原子布尔型浮点型API:¶

模块atomic_boolfloat

shared_atomic.atomic_boolfloat.bool_compare_and_set(v: _cffi_backend._CDataBase, e: _cffi_backend._CDataBase, n: bool) → bool¶

Compare and set atomically. This compares the contents of v with the contents of e. If equal, the operation is a read-modify-write operation that writes n into self. If they are not equal, the operation is a read and the current contents of v are written into e. :param v: pointer of v :param e: pointer of e :param n: value to be set :return: whether the contents of v and contents of e is the same

class shared_atomic.atomic_boolfloat.atomic_bool(value: bool, mode: str = 'singleprocessing')¶

constructor to initialize the atomic_bool, the atomic_bool should be no longer than 8 bytes

Parameters

  • value – initial value of the bool.

  • mode – the mode in which the bool will be shared. ‘singleprocessing’ or ‘s’ for single process, ‘multiprocessing’ or ‘m’ for multiprocessing, on windows platform, only singleprocessing is supported, setting it to ‘m’ or ‘multiprocessing’ will be ignored.

bool_compare_and_set(e: self_atomic_bool, n: bool) → bool¶

Compare and set atomically. This compares the contents of v with the contents of e. If equal, the operation is a read-modify-write operation that writes n into self. If they are not equal, the operation is a read and the current contents of v are written into e. :param e: atomic_bool :param n: value to be set :return: whether the contents of v and contents of e is the same
